or in terms of operators formula_15 
:formula_16
where we have written formula_17, the tangent vectors to the curves which are simply the coordinate grid itself.

If we adopt a new coordinates system formula_18 then for each &quot;i&quot;, the old coordinate formula_19 can be expressed as function of the new system, so formula_20
Let formula_21 be the basis, tangent vectors in this new coordinates system. We can express formula_22 in the new system by applying the chain rule on &quot;x&quot;. As a function of coordinates we find the following transformation
:formula_23
which indeed is the same as the covariant transformation for the derivative of a function.

==Contravariant transformation==

The &quot;components&quot; of a (tangent) vector transform in a different way, called contravariant transformation. Consider a tangent vector v and call its components formula_24 on a basis formula_22. On another basis formula_26 we call the components formula_27, so
